$interpreted: Soldier: What do you think you're doing? Stand still!
Rune: Can't find Sophie...Sophie? Sophie!
Miranda: Master! Where's Master!
Soldier: Nobody move!
Soldier: If you don't stand still, I'll have to forcibly arrest you for taking part in a mob.
Miranda: What a drag! Move it!!
Miranda: Three...two...one! I counted down and there was no reaction. He must be knocked out.
Miranda: Damn, wasting my time...if I don't find Master fast...
Sanchez: *tisk*...a man may be tough, but hell hath no fury like a woman scorned...
Rune: That's not a compliment. But as this fellow's disciple, at least you can protect yourself——
Miranda: Protect myself? No, I'm worried my Master is going to hurt somebody!
Dock Worker: Charge! Don't be afraid. Let's get our money back!
Sophie: Ouch!
Law: Young Lady, are you alright?
Law: Ladies and Gentlemen, settle down. Violence will most certainly not solve anything. We must use reason...
Law: One…
Law: Screw this, I'm not counting! THREE!!!
Sophie: Ru-yi! Hutchinson! Hanbei! Is everyone okay!?
Dock Worker: Just go die already!
Rune: Sophie...are you alright...?
Sophie: I'm fine...
Sophie: ...Huh? Isn't that the thief we just knocked around?
Law: Miranda, thy actions are much too impulsive.
Law: I've admonished thee countless times. For myself and other martial artists, the first skill to be mastered is to master one's unyielding nature.
Ru-yi: Umm...did YOU say that SHE is impulsive...?
Hanbei: Shhh...forget it. He's busy managing his disciple. Probably didn't hear.
Hutchinson: Rogue Gentlemen? Gentleman Rogue? Regardless, a true gentleman, that's for sure...
Soldier: Back up! Back up! Everyone quiet!
Dock Worker: Get out of here! We're just taking back what's ours!
Soldier: General, you can leave this up to us. There's no need for you to be bothered by this.
Dock Worker: Look...
Anxious Citizen: Shhh!
Lazer: Enough! Your appeal has been heard. Queen Diana is dealing with it now. I'd advise you to give it up now.
Lazer: Otherwise, even if the Queen isn't willing, the military will be forced to banish you.
Dock Manager: *spit*...We're not listening to a darn chameleon!
Soldier: He's got balls talking to General Lazer like that——
Dock Worker: We gave up counting on that useless Queen a long time ago! The reason we can't go out to sea and make some money is because of her!
Dock Worker: That's right, it's all the Queen's fault! Tell her to get out of here! That sneaky chameleon should leave the Desert Kingdom as well.
Lazer: The Queen cares more about your lives than any—
Dock Manager: If the Queen really cared she wouldn't levy such a heavy tax on us!
Misa: Everybody lower your weapons, please.
Dock Worker: ...Holy Maiden!
Dock Manager: It's the Blessed Misa and the HIgh Priest Devious!
Devious: Citizens of the Serpent Gods, you have endured suffering. The Holy Maiden has heard your pain and cries of sorrow.
Dock Worker: *gasp*...my mother drank Holy Water prayed over by the Holy Maiden and her deformed leg began to work again!
Dock Manager: Same thing happened when my daughter had a high fever. Thanks to the Holy Maiden's prayers...
Misa: Help them up.
Religious Cleric: Blessed Holy Maiden.
Misa: I understand your suffering.
Devious: Everybody relax. The Holy Maiden will take your request to the Queen. If the Queen still will not listen...
Devious: Trust me when I say that the Snake God will not be forgiving!
Dock Manager: Holy Maiden, we can trust you...
Dock Worker: Holy Maiden, I beg you to save us...
Misa: My words represent the will of the Snake Gods. They are not to be questioned.
Misa: Now is the time that we get through our suffering together. Everybody must listen closely. There will be no violence.
Dock Worker: If that's what the Holy Maiden wants...
Dock Manager: I'm willing to let the Snake Gods and the Holy Maiden protect us...
Devious: Apologies for arriving late. Next time let the Holy Shrine deal with such matters. You can focus on protecting the Queen. We have different duties.
Devious: After all, what the people want it is obvious...
Lazer: ...There won't be a next time.
Devious: I wish this were so. The Holy Maiden's body is rather frail~
Lazer: (What are you doing here...?)
Sophie: That's strange, that girl was so weak just a bit ago...
Miranda: Master, we ought to set out.
Law: Indeed. Due to this nonsense, I have already wasted too much time...
Sophie: Where are you heading?
Law: I'll follow Miranda on her journey to the Kingdom of the Sun. She will participate in the East Alliance's formal testing in the martial arts.
Miranda: ...Apologies. It was I who was mistaken. I was in the wrong.
Sanchez: Does the apology have any use? I got the crap beaten out of me all of the sudden!
Sanchez: You female dog, I ought to——
Rune: It's okay. It's a mistake. It's nothing. Everything...is okay.
Sanchez: Rune, don't you try to stop me!
Rune: Forget it. Miranda is...pretty. We'll meet again...
Sanchez: Again with the women! I got you all wrong, Rune! I...I...ahhh...ahhh!!!!!
Law: Not a problem. Not a problem at all. Thank you most sincerely for taking care of Miranda. We most certainly shall meet again!
Sophie: We ought to head back as well...
Sophie: Oh! Of course!
Sophie: Could it be the person we were looking for...
Maria: Master.
Clark: Maria, how many times have I told you that our relationship is not master-slave. You can call me by my first name.
Maria: Yes sir, Master Clark.
Clark: ...Just Clark is fine.
Maria: Okay. Is this an order from Master Clark?
Clark: ...Yup. It's an order. Let's just call it an order...
Maria: I understand.
Maria: Clark, there are some people staring at you.
Clark: Huh...?
